# Day 7 – Student Database 🎓

## What it does
A terminal app that collects data for 3 students
(name, age, city), stores them as dictionaries
in a list, and displays all records. Also demonstrates
live data modification after storage.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3 (built-in only)

## How to run
python student.py

## What I learned
- List of dictionaries as a simple database
- Input validation with try/except ValueError
- Modifying dictionary values after storage
- Functions that build and append dictionaries

## Output
Prints all student records before and after
modifying the first student's age.
